{
  "texts": [
    "These models often involve millions of parameters and rely on complex patterns and correlations that are difficult to decipher.",
    "This complexity can raise concerns about bias, privacy, ethics, fairness, and transparency.",
    "To address these concerns, XAI refers to the capability of AI systems to provide understandable and interpretable explanations for their decisions and actions, techniques that aim to enhance the comprehensibility and transparency of AI models.",
    "In this study, the LRP technique is used to determine which features of the DL model are responsible for specific predictions.",
    "For enhancing the explainability of networks utilizing the back-propagation algorithm, one of the principal algorithms employed is LRP 68."
  ]
}